Assignment-2.4
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Box Model</title>
</head>
<style>
    body{
        font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;
        line-height: 2;
        padding: 10px;
        margin: 0;
    }
    h1{
        text-align: center;
        font-size: xx-large;
    }
    section{
        height: 160px;
        width: 300px;
        background-color: lightskyblue;
        padding: 15px;
        margin: 2px auto;
        border: 4px;
    }
    .content-box{
        box-sizing: content-box;
    }
    .border-box {
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }
    .effect-box {
        width: 300px;
        height: 80px;
        background-color: rgb(173, 235, 16);
        padding: 15px;
        border: 5px solid #32ff2b;
        line-height: 20px;
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }
</style>
<body>
    <h1> Box Model</h1>
    <section>
        <h2> Content Box </h2>
        <div class="content-box"> It is nothing but the area which your content is displayed </div>

    </section>
    <section>
        <h2> Border Box </h2>
        <div class="border-box"> It tells the browser to account for any border and padding in the values like height and width  </div>
    </section>
    <section>
         <h2> Effect Box</h2>
         <div class="effect-box"> It demonstrates the effect of padding, border and margin </div>
      </section>
</body>
</html>
